Let $$S = \left\{ {n \in N\left| {{{\left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; i  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)}^n}\left( {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   c &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right) = \left( {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   c &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right)\forall a,b,c,d \in R} \right.} \right\}$$, where i = $$\sqrt { - 1} $$. Then the number of 2-digit numbers in the set S is _____________.

_children.explanation:
Let $$X = \left( {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   c &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ &amp; $$A = {\left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; i  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)^n}$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ AX = IX<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ A = I<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {\left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; i  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)^n} = I$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {A^8} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ n is multiple of 8<br><br>So, number of 2 digit numbers in the set <br><br>S = 11 (16, 24, 32, .........., 96)
